[3] Nigeria (Maiduguri): IDP camp
Date: Tue 12 Jul 2016, 4:44 PM
Source: Daily Trust [edited]
http://www.dailytrust.com.ng/news/general/measles-kills-6-in-maiduguri-idp-camp/155050.html


An outbreak of measles at the ATC Internally Displaced Camp in Maiduguri killed 6 children while 22 people are affected. Officials at the camp attribute the outbreak to congestion as the camp had over 8000 IDPs when the disease broke out.

Consequently, officials said 1913 IDPs from Gwoza have been evacuated to Bakassi IDP camp while 345 IDPs from Askira Uba have been returned to their community. Despite the decongestion, officials said the camp is struggling with lack of drugs and doctors.

Millions of people were displaced from their homes as a result of Boko Haram's insurgency in Borno, Adamawa and Yobe states.

[Byline: Shehu Abubakar]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Maiduguri, also called Yerwa by its locals] is the capital and the largest city of Borno State in north-eastern Nigeria. The city sits along the seasonal Ngadda River which disappears into the Firki swamps in the areas around Lake Chad.
It appears internally displaced persons (IDPs) must make a choice between returning home to an area that may not have been fully liberated from the Boko Haram terrorists vs. staying in the poor overcrowded living conditions in their camp. A difficult situation.

A map of Borno State, Nigeria, can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4357193,621. - Mod.LK]
